Corporate Sustainability



       	                    

                           	             

                                                        
                            Initiated in 1999, our Corporate Sustainability Assessment (CSA) is an annual assessment of companies’ sustainability practices. Our approach is unique in that it is based on information provided by the companies directly through the online questionnaire. Based on a rigorous and rules-based methodology, the CSA forms the research backbone of the globally recognized Dow Jones Sustainability Indices.

 

We also use the insights derived from the CSA in our entire range of asset management products and services. Our Sustainability Services offering allows companies, experts and practitioners to evaluate their sustainability performance against that of their peers.
                            
						


 
 


